705299f-a.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Tilden Avenue
705299f-a.folder: Kings Highway & Tilden Avenue, Brooklyn, NY

705298f-c.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Tilden Avenue
705298f-c.text:
(1)
King's Highway, at the S.E. corner of Tilden Ave., showing the
Flatlands Neck Sabbath Church. The congregation of this Church were in-
corporated in 1867. Originally it was a Sabbath School, and it was es-
tablished by John Remsen on land donated by him to the people of the
'Neck''.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, at a later date.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same as No. 2, from another angle. Because of the widening
of King's Highway, the building will be moved.back.to the new curb line.,
March 1925.
Euiene L. Armbruster Collaction.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
